documentation.value:
Prints a message to the standard output stream followed by a newline.

```java
System.out.println("Hello, World!");
System.out.println(42);
System.out.println("Value: " + x);
```

Prints a message to the standard output stream without a trailing newline.

```java
System.out.print("Enter name: ");
System.out.print(value);
```

Prints a formatted string to the standard output stream using format specifiers.

```java
System.out.printf("Name: %s, Age: %d%n", name, age);
System.out.printf("%.2f%n", 3.14159);
System.out.printf("%10s | %5d%n", item, count);
```

Prints a message to the standard error stream followed by a newline.

```java
System.err.println("Error: something went wrong");
System.err.println(exception.getMessage());
```

Declares a new public class. The file name must match the class name.

```java
public class MyClass {
    // fields and methods
}
```

Restricts access to the declaring class only.

```java
private int count;
private void helper() { }
```

Allows access within the same package and subclasses.

```java
protected String name;
protected void init() { }
```

Declares a class-level member that belongs to the class rather than instances.

```java
public static int count = 0;
public static void main(String[] args) { }
```

Prevents modification: final variables cannot be reassigned, final methods cannot be overridden, final classes cannot be extended.

```java
final int MAX = 100;
final List<String> items = new ArrayList<>();
```

Declares an abstract class or method. Abstract classes cannot be instantiated; abstract methods must be implemented by subclasses.

```java
public abstract class Shape {
    public abstract double area();
}
```

Declares an interface that classes can implement.

```java
public interface Drawable {
    void draw();
    default void reset() { }
}
```

Indicates that a class inherits from a superclass.

```java
public class Dog extends Animal {
    // inherited and new members
}
```

Indicates that a class implements one or more interfaces.

```java
public class Circle implements Drawable, Serializable {
    // implement interface methods
}
```

Creates a new instance of a class by invoking its constructor.

```java
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
MyClass obj = new MyClass(arg1, arg2);
```

Returns a value from a method or exits a void method.

```java
return result;
return x + y;
return;
```

Throws an exception to be caught by a try-catch block or propagated up the call stack.

```java
throw new IllegalArgumentException("Invalid value: " + value);
throw new RuntimeException("Unexpected error", cause);
```

Declares that a method may throw checked exceptions.

```java
public void readFile(String path) throws IOException {
    // may throw IOException
}
```

Wraps code that may throw exceptions and handles them gracefully.

```java
try {
    // risky code
} catch (Exception e) {
    e.printStackTrace();
} finally {
    // cleanup
}
```

Automatically closes resources that implement AutoCloseable when the block exits.

```java
try (var reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader(path))) {
    String line = reader.readLine();
} catch (IOException e) {
    e.printStackTrace();
}
```

Ensures only one thread at a time can execute the synchronized code, providing mutual exclusion.

```java
synchronized (lock) {
    // thread-safe code
}

public synchronized void update() { }
```

Tests whether an object is an instance of a specific type. Supports pattern matching (Java 16+).

```java
if (obj instanceof String s) {
    System.out.println(s.length());
}
if (animal instanceof Dog) { }
```

A switch expression that yields a value using arrow syntax.

```java
String result = switch (day) {
    case MONDAY, FRIDAY -> "Work";
    case SATURDAY, SUNDAY -> "Rest";
    default -> "Unknown";
};
```

Declares a record — a concise immutable data carrier that auto-generates equals, hashCode, toString, and accessor methods.

```java
public record Point(int x, int y) { }
public record Person(String name, int age) { }
```

Infers the type of a local variable from the initializer expression.

```java
var list = new ArrayList<String>();
var map = Map.of("key", "value");
var count = 0;
```

Returns the string representation of the argument.

```java
String s = String.valueOf(42);
String s = String.valueOf(true);
String s = String.valueOf(charArray);
```

Returns a formatted string using the specified format string and arguments.

```java
String s = String.format("Name: %s, Age: %d", name, age);
String s = String.format("%.2f", price);
```

Returns a new String composed of elements joined together with the specified delimiter.

```java
String csv = String.join(", ", "a", "b", "c");
String path = String.join("/", parts);
```

Returns the number of characters in the string.

```java
int len = str.length();
if (name.length() > 0) { }
```

Returns the char value at the specified index.

```java
char c = str.charAt(0);
char last = str.charAt(str.length() - 1);
```

Returns a substring from the specified begin index to the end index.

```java
String sub = str.substring(0, 5);
String rest = str.substring(3);
```

Compares this string to the specified object for content equality.

```java
if (str.equals("hello")) { }
if (a.equals(b)) { }
```

Returns true if this string contains the specified sequence of characters.

```java
if (str.contains("search")) { }
boolean found = text.contains(keyword);
```

Returns the index of the first occurrence of the specified substring, or -1 if not found.

```java
int idx = str.indexOf("find");
int pos = str.indexOf('@');
```

Returns a string with all occurrences of the target replaced by the replacement.

```java
String result = str.replace("old", "new");
String clean = str.replace(" ", "");
```

Replaces each substring matching the given regular expression with the replacement.

```java
String clean = str.replaceAll("\\s+", " ");
String digits = str.replaceAll("[^0-9]", "");
```

Splits this string around matches of the given regular expression.

```java
String[] parts = str.split(",");
String[] words = str.split("\\s+");
```

Converts this string to a new character array.

```java
char[] chars = str.toCharArray();
for (char c : str.toCharArray()) { }
```

Tells whether this string matches the given regular expression.

```java
boolean valid = email.matches("[\\w.]+@[\\w.]+");
if (str.matches("\\d+")) { }
```

Returns an unmodifiable list containing the specified elements.

```java
List<String> names = List.of("Alice", "Bob", "Charlie");
List<Integer> nums = List.of(1, 2, 3);
```

A resizable-array implementation of the List interface.

```java
List<String> list = new ArrayList<>();
List<Integer> nums = new ArrayList<>(List.of(1, 2, 3));
list.add("item");
```

A doubly-linked list implementation of the List and Deque interfaces.

```java
LinkedList<String> list = new LinkedList<>();
list.addFirst("first");
list.addLast("last");
```

Hash table based implementation of the Map interface. Permits null keys and values.

```java
Map<String, Integer> map = new HashMap<>();
map.put("key", 42);
int val = map.getOrDefault("key", 0);
```

A NavigableMap implementation based on a Red-Black tree. Keys are sorted in natural order or by a provided Comparator.

```java
TreeMap<String, Integer> map = new TreeMap<>();
map.put("banana", 2);
map.firstKey(); // smallest key
```

Implements the Set interface backed by a hash table. Does not guarantee iteration order.

```java
Set<String> set = new HashSet<>();
set.add("item");
boolean exists = set.contains("item");
```

A NavigableSet implementation based on a TreeMap. Elements are sorted in natural order or by a provided Comparator.

```java
TreeSet<Integer> sorted = new TreeSet<>();
sorted.add(3);
sorted.add(1);
sorted.first(); // 1
```

Sorts the specified list into ascending order according to natural ordering or a provided Comparator.

```java
Collections.sort(list);
Collections.sort(list, Comparator.reverseOrder());
```

Sorts the specified array into ascending numerical order.

```java
Arrays.sort(arr);
Arrays.sort(arr, Comparator.reverseOrder());
```

Returns an unmodifiable Map.Entry containing the specified key and value.

```java
Map.Entry<String, Integer> e = Map.entry("key", 42);
Map<String, Integer> map = Map.ofEntries(Map.entry("a", 1));
```

Returns a sequential Stream with this collection as its source.

```java
list.stream().filter(x -> x > 0).collect(Collectors.toList());
set.stream().map(String::toUpperCase).toList();
```

Performs a mutable reduction operation on stream elements using a Collector.

```java
List<String> result = stream.collect(Collectors.toList());
Map<String, List<Item>> grouped = items.stream()
    .collect(Collectors.groupingBy(Item::category));
```

Performs a reduction on the elements using an associative accumulation function.

```java
int sum = list.stream().reduce(0, Integer::sum);
Optional<String> concat = list.stream().reduce(String::concat);
```

Performs an action for each element of the stream.

```java
list.forEach(System.out::println);
map.forEach((k, v) -> System.out.println(k + "=" + v));
```

Returns a Collector that concatenates stream elements into a single String.

```java
String csv = list.stream().collect(Collectors.joining(", "));
String wrapped = list.stream().collect(Collectors.joining(", ", "[", "]"));
```

Returns true if a value is present.

```java
if (opt.isPresent()) {
    System.out.println(opt.get());
}
```

Returns the value if present, otherwise returns the specified default.

```java
String name = opt.orElse("Unknown");
int val = optInt.orElse(0);
```

Returns the value if present, otherwise throws an exception produced by the supplier.

```java
String name = opt.orElseThrow(() -> new NoSuchElementException("Not found"));
String val = opt.orElseThrow();
```

If a value is present, performs the given action with the value.

```java
opt.ifPresent(System.out::println);
opt.ifPresent(val -> process(val));
```

Creates and starts a new thread of execution.

```java
Thread t = new Thread(() -> {
    System.out.println("Running in thread");
});
t.start();
```

A functional interface for tasks that can be executed by a thread.

```java
Runnable task = () -> System.out.println("task");
new Thread(task).start();
```

Manages a pool of threads for executing tasks.

```java
ExecutorService executor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);
executor.submit(() -> doWork());
executor.shutdown();
```

Represents the result of an asynchronous computation. Use get() to retrieve the result.

```java
Future<String> future = executor.submit(() -> compute());
String result = future.get();
```

A task that returns a result and may throw an exception. Like Runnable but with a return value.

```java
Callable<Integer> task = () -> {
    return computeValue();
};
Future<Integer> future = executor.submit(task);
```

Reads all content from a file into a string.

```java
String content = Files.readString(Path.of("file.txt"));
String data = Files.readString(path, StandardCharsets.UTF_8);
```

Writes a CharSequence to a file.

```java
Files.writeString(Path.of("output.txt"), content);
Files.writeString(path, data, StandardOpenOption.APPEND);
```

Returns a Path by converting a path string or URI.

```java
Path p = Path.of("src", "main", "java");
Path file = Path.of("/tmp/data.txt");
```

Reads text from a character-input stream with buffering for efficient reading.

```java
try (var reader = new BufferedReader(new FileReader("file.txt"))) {
    String line;
    while ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {
        System.out.println(line);
    }
}
```

A simple text scanner for parsing primitive types and strings using regular expressions.

```java
Scanner scanner = new Scanner(System.in);
String name = scanner.nextLine();
int num = scanner.nextInt();
scanner.close();
```

Returns the greater of two values.

```java
int max = Math.max(a, b);
double bigger = Math.max(3.14, 2.71);
```

Returns a random double value between 0.0 (inclusive) and 1.0 (exclusive).

```java
double r = Math.random();
int dice = (int)(Math.random() * 6) + 1;
```

Parses the string argument as a signed decimal integer.

```java
int num = Integer.parseInt("42");
int hex = Integer.parseInt("FF", 16);
```

Returns true if the arguments are equal to each other and false otherwise. Handles null safely.

```java
boolean eq = Objects.equals(a, b);
if (Objects.equals(name, "admin")) { }
```

The entry point for a Java application.

```java
public static void main(String[] args) {
    System.out.println("Hello, World!");
}
```

Iterates over each element of an array or Iterable.

```java
for (String item : list) {
    System.out.println(item);
}
```

A traditional index-based for loop.

```java
for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    System.out.println(i);
}
```
